===Etymology===
[[File:Brown_Bear_Cubs_2.jpg|thumb|A Kodiak brown bear cub with a white stripe]]
{{zh-ref|Zhang (2019)}} observes that juveniles of certain [[brown bear]] subspecies display white chest stripes that fade with age, matching the description {{lang|zh|黃白文}} in ''{{w|Erya}}'' and ''{{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}''; therefore, she proposes that {{och-l|羆|tr=*praj}} is cognate to {{och-l|斑|tr=*prân}} "stripe, striped", both being from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*pral}}. As {{och-l|斑|tr=*prân}} is possibly the same word as {{och-l|班|tr=*prân}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}), see {{och-l|班|tr=*prân}} for more etymology.

Meanwhile, {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai (2019)}} compare {{och-l|羆|tr= *praj}} to Brag-bar {{cog|sit-sit|prī||Asiatic brown bear}}, Cogtse {{cog|sit-sit|prī||[[idem]]}}, and {{cog|sit-jap|pri||[[idem]]}}.

